titleproper.value: Guide to the Time Inc. Invitational Records<lb/>1982-1989<lb/> <num>MS 3009-RG 29</num>

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2019-11-27T14:54:27</date>

abstract.value:
The Time Inc. Invitational was an annual invitation-only sports competition event organized by the
magazines' Advertising Sales Departments and held at the Maidstone Club in East Hamptons, NY. Records include the planning and event materials for the years 1983 to 1985, 1987, and 1989.

p.value: Open to qualified researchers. Materials created within the past 35 years also may be subject to restriction on a case-by-case basis. Unreformatted audiovisual and digital material in the collection is not accessible. Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use.
This collection should be cited as Time Inc. Invitational Records, MS 3009-RG29, New-York Historical Society.

Guests included presidents and other senior executives, media directors, advertising managers, and account managers from companies that advertised in Time Inc. publications. Companies included AT&T, Grey Advertising, McCann-Erickson, Ogilvy & Mather, Panasonic, and Seagram. Some years guests were given the option of taking the Time Inc. jet to and from the event.

The Time Inc. Invitational Records represent the Invitationals from 1983 to 1985, 1987, and 1989. Materials include planning binders, schedules of events, expense reports, bills, receipts, guest lists and invitations, response cards, rules of play, realia such as buttons and customized pencils and golf tees, samples of printed material with the logo, bills and receipts, logistical materials such as maps to the accommodations and transportation arrangements, videotapes of events, digital material which may be duplicates of printed material, and other event planning material.
